modules.description: Provides functions to create and manipulate configuration objects with error handling capabilities. Works with custom types for error handlers and configuration states. Used to set default values and suppress error notifications in application setup workflows.

Provides asynchronous search operations for lists and arrays, supporting early termination upon finding a matching element. Works with lazy and strict data structures, including lists, arrays, and sequences. Enables efficient filtering in I/O-bound tasks such as searching through network responses or file contents.

Manages configuration setup with custom error handling, enabling default value assignment and error suppression. Key types include configuration states and error handlers, supporting operations like validation and modification. Users can define custom error responses and automate configuration defaults during application initialization. Examples include silencing non-critical warnings and pre-filling missing settings with fallback values.
